Quote: He bought a coastal farm which borders the Whangape Harbour, in Northland, and then proceeded to place a Queen Elizabeth II National Trust open-space covenant over 130 ha of it, thus ensuring public access to the coast in perpetuity... [82] Each has agreed to a permanent open-space convenant for their special place, enacting conditions and prohibitions designed to keep the area in its natural space.
